In a bowl, combine the salsa and tomato sauce; spread half in an 11-in. x 7-in. x 2-in. baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. In a skillet, saute the carrot, zucchini, mushrooms, onions and garlic in oil until crisp-tender. remove from the heat. stir in the cheeses, egg substitute and basil. Stuff into pasta shells; place in prepared baking dish. Top with the remaining salsa mixture. Cover and bake at 350 degrees F for 40-45 minutes or until heated through.